headline: Stocks Set for Muted Open After Trump’s Tariff Threats, Big Tech Earnings and Fed Meeting in Focus
summary: March S&P 500 E-Mini futures (ESH26) are down -0.05%, and March Nasdaq 100 E-Mini futures (NQH26) are down -0.14% this morning, pointing to a muted open on Wall Street as President Trump’s tariff threats against Canada and the looming risk of a partial U.S. government shutdown curbed risk appetite at the start of a busy week.

headline: Tech Rebound Soothes Greenland-Induced Shivers, Just As Earnings Season Hits Its Stride
summary: With only 13% of companies reporting thus far, S&P 500 EPS growth for Q4 currently stands at 8.2%. Headline whiplash impacted US markets last week. The tech sector continues to dominate.

headline: 3 Market-Beating Stocks to Target This Week
summary: Stocks that outperform the market usually share key traits such as rising sales, expanding margins, and increasing returns on capital. The select few that can do all three for many years are often the ones that make you life-changing money.
